      <section eId="sec_CCRP-893-1">
        <num>CCRP 893.1</num>
        <heading>893.1. Â Motion to invoke firearm sentencing provision</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-893-1__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>If the district attorney intends to move for imposition of sentence under the provisions of Article 893.3, he shall file a motion within a reasonable period of time prior to commencement of trial of the felony or specifically enumerated misdemeanor in which the firearm was used.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-893-1__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The motion shall contain a plain, concise, and definite written statement of the essential facts constituting the basis for the motion and shall specify the provisions of this Chapter under which the district attorney intends to proceed.
Added by</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112883</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
